# Testing

## Coverage

- Target: ≥ 80% line coverage on new code (enforced by Gate 3).
- Coverage is a floor, not a ceiling — prefer meaningful tests over hitting
  the number.

## Layers

| Layer | What to test | Tool |
|---|---|---|
| Unit | pure functions, no I/O | language default (JUnit / pytest / vitest / go test) |
| Integration | module composition, real I/O against a stub | same tool, separate suite |
| E2E | user-visible flows | Playwright / Cypress / Selenium |

## Naming

- Unit test files: `<name>.test.<ext>` next to the source file.
- Test names describe behavior: `it("returns 404 when user is missing", ...)`.

## What to skip

- Don't test third-party libraries.
- Don't test private helpers indirectly via reflection — test the public API.
- Don't write snapshot tests for objects that change shape every iteration.
